      - generic [ref=e238]:
        - heading "Learn more about senior living and senior care" [level=2] [ref=e239]
        - paragraph [ref=e241]:
          - text: There are multiple types of care and communities available, so it's
          - text: important to know which is the best fit for your needs.
        - generic [ref=e242]:
          - generic [ref=e243]:
            - img [ref=e245]
            - paragraph [ref=e248]: Assisted living
            - paragraph [ref=e250]:
              - text: At costs ranging from $1,200 to $8,000 per month,
              - link "assisted living" [ref=e251] [cursor=pointer]:
                - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-living/assisted-living
              - text: communities are a great choice for someone who needs help with activities of daily living, such as eating, grooming and bathing. Many also offer respite care (short-term stays).
            - link "Learn More" [ref=e253] [cursor=pointer]:
              - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-living/assisted-living
          - generic [ref=e254]:
            - img [ref=e256]
            - paragraph [ref=e259]: Memory care
            - paragraph [ref=e261]:
              - link "Memory care" [ref=e262] [cursor=pointer]:
                - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-living/memory-care-facilities
              - text: communities are specially designed living environments for people with Alzheimer's or other dementias. You can expect that staff members have extra training to help people with memory loss. Costs are $3,000 per month and up. Some also provide respite care.
            - link "Learn More" [ref=e264] [cursor=pointer]:
              - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-living/memory-care-facilities
          - generic [ref=e265]:
            - img [ref=e267]
            - paragraph [ref=e270]: In-home care
            - paragraph [ref=e272]:
              - text: For help with driving, getting around the house, meal preparation, companionship, and light housekeeping, hire a professional caregiver through an
              - link "in-home care" [ref=e273] [cursor=pointer]:
                - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-care/in-home-care
              - text: agency. Caregivers can be hired on a one-time basis or a regular monthly schedule. Rates usually range from $20 to $40 per hour.
            - link "Learn More" [ref=e275] [cursor=pointer]:
              - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-care/in-home-care
          - generic [ref=e276]:
            - img [ref=e278]
            - paragraph [ref=e281]: Independent living
            - paragraph [ref=e283]:
              - link "Independent living" [ref=e284] [cursor=pointer]:
                - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-living/independent-living
              - text: communities are great for residents who want to enjoy the perks of community living, but who don't need regular assistance with activities of daily living. Costs range from $1,000 to $4,000 per month.
            - link "Learn More" [ref=e286] [cursor=pointer]:
              - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-living/independent-living
          - generic [ref=e287]:
            - img [ref=e289]
            - paragraph [ref=e292]: Nursing homes
            - paragraph [ref=e294]:
              - text: Also called skilled nursing facilities (SNFs),
              - link "nursing homes" [ref=e295] [cursor=pointer]:
                - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-living/nursing-homes
              - text: are staffed by skilled medical professionals who can provide 24-hour support. Some also offer short-term stays for someone who is transferring from the hospital but not yet ready to go home.
            - link "Learn More" [ref=e297] [cursor=pointer]:
              - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-living/nursing-homes
          - generic [ref=e298]:
            - img [ref=e300]
            - paragraph [ref=e303]: Hospice
            - paragraph [ref=e305]:
              - link "Hospice care" [ref=e306] [cursor=pointer]:
                - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-care/hospices
              - text: helps provide comfort to your loved one in their last days. Care teams specialize in keeping pain and suffering to a minimum. This care is often provided at home, but care teams can also go to a hospital or other care facility to provide relief.
            - link "Learn More" [ref=e308] [cursor=pointer]:
              - /url: https://www.caring.com/senior-care/hospices
